<TITLE> 12 BCL activists held over Tejgaon clashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 14 (bdnews24.com)Twelve activists of Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL), the student wing of the ruling Awami League, were arrested from the hostels of Tejgaon Polytechnic Institute on Monday night after factional clashes. Besides, 23 students, all BCL activists, were detained. Police recovered 17 sharp weapons, clubs, GI pipe, iron rods and stamps from Latif hostel at that time, said Chowdhury Manjurul Kabir, deputy commissioner of Tejgaon region, at a press conference at Tejgaon Police Station on Tuesday. Chase, counter-chase and clashes took place among the four factions of BCL, led by 'Zakir', 'Shahin', 'Kamalesh' and 'Imtiaz', at around 1:30pm to dominate the campus. The students fought each other locally made weapons, clubs and stones. Police later raided Latif hostel, Zahir Raihan hostel and Motahar Hossain hostel at around 11:30 pm and detained 35 students. Twelve, identified to have wielded weapons from pictures published in newspapers, were arrested. The rest, four among them outsiders, were detained as suspects and were being quizzed, Kabir said. Seven ramdas, five machetes, four small knives and a chapati are among the sharp weapons. The arrestees are Rakib Islam Masud, Salman Hasan, Abu Naser, Ruhul Amin, Shika Russell, Kausar Alam, Tanzirul Islam Rahim, Mostafa Milon, Enamul Hasan, Farhad Hossain, Alim Raj and Al-Ikram Nixon. ASM Mahtab, assistant commissioner of Tejgaon region, and Shyamol Mukharjee, assistant commissioner of public relations of DMP were present there.
